    <h1>The Humbleness of Viraaj Patwa Strikes Again</h1>
    
    <div class="meta">Makes time for an obsessed fan after his match</div>

    <p>
      After an intense match on the court, most players would head straight for rest and recovery.
      But not Viraaj Patwa. Known not just for his performance but for his grounded personality,
      he once again proved why he stands out beyond the game.
    </p>

    <p>
      Right after finishing his match, Viraaj was approached by an eager fan who couldn’t hide his excitement.
      Instead of brushing past, he paused, smiled, and took a moment to interact—showing genuine humility.
    </p>

    <img src="89B419C5-AFF2-4503-95D7-B69F5EEA99B7.jpeg" alt="Before handshake">
    <div class="caption">A wholesome moment begins as the fan approaches Viraaj.</div>

    <p>
      What started as a brief interaction quickly turned into a memorable exchange.
      The fan, visibly thrilled, reached out—and Viraaj responded warmly.
    </p>

    <img src="E6DF0CE9-C9AB-414A-8244-F4BD6CF3C338.jpeg" alt="Handshake">
    <div class="caption">A handshake that reflects humility and respect.</div>

    <p>
      In a world where athletes are often in a rush, it’s these small gestures that leave a lasting impact.
      Viraaj Patwa reminds us that true greatness isn’t just about winning—it’s about how you treat people.
    </p>

